HEADWORD: Hoarseness
<hw>Hoarse"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Harshness or
roughness of voice or sound, due to mucus collected on the vocal cords,
or to swelling or looseness of the cords.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

